sourceRange -

Reparents the contents of the range to the given nodeand inserts the node at the position of the start of therange.

Parameters:
newParent - The node to surround the contents with.
Throws:

HIERARCHY_REQUEST_ERR: Raised if the container of the start of the Range is of a type that does not allow children ofthe type of newParent or if newParent is an ancestor of thecontaineror if node would end up with a child node of a type not allowedby the type of node.
RangeException - BAD_ENDPOINTS_ERR: Raised if the range partially selects a non-text node.
INVALID_NODE_TYPE_ERR: Raised ifnode is an Attr, Entity, DocumentType, Notation,Document, or DocumentFragment node.
